  <main>
    
    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        The Glorious Revolution, also known as the Revolution of 1688, was a significant event in the history of Britain. It took place when William of Orange, a Dutch stadtholder, invaded England and overthrew King James II. The revolution marked the shift from an absolute monarchy to a constitutional monarchy in Britain.
      </p>
      <p>
        For more details, you can visit the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glorious_Revolution" target="_blank">Wikipedia page on the Glorious Revolution</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="causes">
      <h2>Causes</h2>
      <p>
        The Glorious Revolution was primarily driven by political and religious factors. Some key causes include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The fear of Catholicism and the desire for Protestant succession</li>
        <li>Conflicts between King James II and Parliament</li>
        <li>The birth of James II's Catholic son, threatening a Catholic dynasty</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To learn more about the causes, refer to the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Causes_of_the_Glorious_Revolution" target="_blank">Wikipedia page on the causes of the Glorious Revolution</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="events">
      <h2>Events</h2>
      <p>
        The Glorious Revolution unfolded through a series of significant events, including:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>The landing of William of Orange in England</li>
        <li>The flight of James II</li>
        <li>The Convention Parliament</li>
        <li>The Declaration of Rights and the offer of the throne to William and Mary</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        You can find a detailed chronology of events on the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronology_of_the_Glorious_Revolution" target="_blank">Wikipedia page on the chronology of the Glorious Revolution</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    
    <section id="impact">
      <h2>Impact</h2>
      <p>
        The Glorious Revolution had a profound impact on British history, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The establishment of a constitutional monarchy</li>
        <li>The passage of the Bill of Rights</li>
        <li>The decline of the divine right of kings</li>
        <li>The influence on future revolutions, such as the American and French Revolutions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To delve deeper into the impact of the Glorious Revolution, visit the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Effects_of_the_Glorious_Revolution" target="_blank">Wikipedia page on the effects of the Glorious Revolution</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
    
